Sentencas: In the development of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC), the anode supported thin electrolyte with higher conductivity than YSZ is an essential approach in recent years.
Titulo: Co-sintering of SDC/NiO-SDC bi-layers prepared by tape casting

Sentencas: In this work, we report our route that Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) as electrolyte and porous NiO-SDC as anode substrate are prepared by a bi-layer tape casting and co-sintering process.
Titulo: Co-sintering of SDC/NiO-SDC bi-layers prepared by tape casting

Sentencas: The major effort was to adjust and control the shrinkage of the two material layers.
Titulo: Co-sintering of SDC/NiO-SDC bi-layers prepared by tape casting

Sentencas: It was found that only the specimens with less than 0.1% mismatching of the sintering shrinkage between two layers can result in the flat and crack free samples.
Titulo: Co-sintering of SDC/NiO-SDC bi-layers prepared by tape casting

Sentencas: In addition, high activity powders were the essential to obtain dense SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Co-sintering of SDC/NiO-SDC bi-layers prepared by tape casting

Sentencas: Fuel cells with Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 as cathode were tested.
Titulo: Co-sintering of SDC/NiO-SDC bi-layers prepared by tape casting

Sentencas: The open circuit voltage (OCV) and the power density of the cells confirmed the full densification of the SDC electrolyte on the anode support.
